post_text:
Yesterday the School Operations Team met to discuss plans for the 2020-21 school year. Information was shared at the BOE meeting last night. Here is the timeline the team is working on.
July 13 - Staff and Family surveys sent out
July 16 - KSDE to release reopening guidance
July 20-30 - Online enrollment
July 22 - Sumner County meeting with schools to discuss reopening guidelines in the county
July 20-24 - Team and staff review the KSDE guidance and develop plan
July 27 - Finalize plan to share with BOE

post_text:
Last night the USD 360 BOE set commencement for 11AM on Saturday, July 18. All KDHE and county health department guidelines in effect at that time will be followed. Should there be restrictions that jeopardize a traditional graduation ceremony alternate plans will be reviewed on how to proceed on that particular date.
The new date should give the students a chance to have a traditional Caldwell graduation ceremony or as close as possible. This should allow time to let families know the new date.
A review of where the state stands on the reopening phases will be discussed again at the July board meeting.

post_text:
PLEASE BE ADVISED
Executive Order No. 20-16 (pg. 6, 9b) issued by Governor Laura Kelly today, establishing a statewide “stay home” order through April 19, doesn’t call for any further changes to current K-12 school operations.
Kansas public and private schools will continue to operate under the following guidelines issued by Governor Kelly on March 17, unless prohibited by a district’s local county health official:
Will will be reducing hours the offices are open. One of the building offices will be open Monday through Wednesday. Limited times each day the central office will be open.
Board meetings are likely to be held on Zoom. More information to come out on meetings.
Buildings will be closed the rest of the week except for essential personnel or to perform essential tasks.
We will only be serving food two days a week, but it will cover five days worth of meals.
Our continuous learning plan will start on Monday, March 30.
We will continue to share information as it comes out to us.

We will only be serving food two days a week, but it will cover five days worth of meals.
Our continuous learning plan will start on Monday, March 30.
We will continue to share information as it comes out to us.

shared_text:
Orion Education & Training
February 6 at 12:00 AM ·

We hosted several school districts today! Student activities for Child Nutrition and Wellness included a scavenger hunt in the morning to find clues and perform tasks related to creating a healthier school environment and modeling level policies in the Kansas School Wellness Policy Guidelines. This afternoon, they created “story walks” to share their own stories on how students can be advocates for creating a healthier school environment.

Child Nutrition & Wellness is hosting five interactive regional workshops focused on actions to implement modeling level wellness policies. Participants hear best practices, gain knowledge, and obtain resources to help their schools envision and create a healthier school environment.

Thanks for visiting USD 254 Barber County North, Argonia USD 359, USD 463 - Udall Schools, USD 312 Haven Public Schools, USD #356 Conway Springs, KS, Augusta Schools USD 402, USD360_Caldwell, Cheney USD 268, and St Margaret Mary School!
